Lomita dos was our go-to Friday night date spot pre-Covid, and it continues to be our favorite part of the week even now. Eric makes us feel like family every time we walk in the door. The entire staff goes out of their way to make you feel comfortable, and they seem to love working there. Their updated safety protocols are on point. I highly recommend the carne asada and enchiladas, and they low key have the best French fries in town! The strong and delicious margaritas make it an awesome night every day of the week!!

I had been coming to this restaurant for years-brought friends, visitors from out of town.  Wanted to give to a family run establishment vs a corporate one. Was there with a couple friends one night for a going away get together as they were moving to San Diego. Unbeknownst to me my friends had gone up and given Eric, the manager,  one hundred and fifty dollars for future meals for me. He told them they didn't have gift certificates but he would take care of it. I am a senior on a fixed income- really nice friends to do that for me. A couple of months later they contacted me and we were catching up. They wanted to know if I was enjoying my meals. I had no idea what they were talking about. They blew their lids when they found out Eric had pocketed the money and never told me. He just kept bringing me a check every time I came in. Who does that to a regular customer who brings in business, a low income senior citizen? I was completely blown away not to mentioned very saddened and disappointed. All I can say is I feel sorry for Eric as nothing good can come from that behavior.

I usually love small, hole in the wall, type Mexican restaurants but the only thing this place did well was disappoint. From the table for 4 even though we were a party of 5 to the small, never refilling tortilla chip basket which 5 people make disappear in a big hurry. I think it's just policy because my soda was never refilled either. The tamale my wife ordered wasn't much more than formed mush that tasted like, well, mush. My fajita salad had that distinctive 'bag salad' taste and cut and the meat was so chewy I swallowed huge chunks because I simply got bored of trying to chew it and needed to move on. The taco on the kids menu didn't include meat. Read that again, a meatless "taco"! It already cost $6 for a kids meatless "taco" and they charged extra to put any on. My other son had an adult taco plate and that was $14 for a taco and rice. I am not from here and maybe this is normal for DC but I've had better Mexican food with better service and at a better price from gas stations. But hey! At least it was outrageously expensive
